headline: Trump's big beautiful bill: What the pharma industry is watching
summary: Pharmaceutical stocks, including Pfizer (PFE), Johnson & Johnson (JNJ), Abbvie (ABBV), Novo Nordisk (NVO), and Astrazeneca (AZN), are falling after President Trump said tariffs on the industry are coming "very soon." Chris Meekins, managing director and Washington health policy research analyst at Raymond James, joins Market Domination to discuss potential tariffs and explain how President Trump's tax bill could affect the pharmaceutical industry. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here.
